how to get wifi working:
connect rpi to laptop with ethernet (& set wifi/ethernet sharing)
arp -a to see list of ips -> find rpi ip (eno1)
ssh user@ip
set up wifi (use sudo):
nmcli connection add type wifi con-name kaist ifname wlan0 ssid "SSID_NAME"
nmcli connection modify kaist wifi-sec.key-mgmt wpa-eap 802-1x.eap peap 802-1x.identity "YOUR_ID" 802-1x.password "YOUR_PASSWORD" 802-1x.phase2-auth mschapv2
nmcli connection up kaist
hostname -I to get wifi ip
unplug ethernet and ssh using wifi ip

setup to avoid entering ip everytime (not sure if this is needed, try sshing with hostname instead of ip first):
on laptop:
sudo apt install avahi-daemon libnss-mdns
sudo systemctl enable --now avahi-daemon
